Edit conf.py.example and rename it to conf.py.

In the 'component' section, set up the credentials that should be used
to connect as a component to the Jabber server.

The 'db' section is used to set up the file name of the SQLite
database used to store registrations.

Also create the table in the database using the file
'registrations.sql'. For example, is the file name of the
database is registrations.db, simply run from the command line:
$ sqlite < registrations.sql registrations.db
